cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.SI

This paper deals with associative memories, which are a fundamental concept in neural networks and machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on sparse associative memories and introduces strategies to efficiently store non-uniform messages. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves analysis and discussion of the introduced methods, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Additionally, the paper deals with artificial intelligence and information theory, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory) likely categories. Finally, the paper presents a practical application example, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
